Why have you put the subtitles permanently on the movie? Storing them in a .srt (.sub etc.) together with the movie will make it easier for non-Swedish to see the movie with their respective subtitles, and will give the opportunity to watch the movie without subtitles. Subtitles stored as images is wasting a lot  more space because .srt (etc) subtitles are pure text.

It is easy, and will make your torrents more popular.

A guide to create these with the program "SubRip" can be found here: http://www.doom9.org/index.html?/subrip.htm
or from the programs website:
http://zuggy.wz.cz/

And the program can be found on its project page on sourceforge.net: 
http://sourceforge.net/projects/subrip/

I hope you will do this in your next relaeses.
